My responsibilities can be broken up into roughly 3 main categories...Development:  I architect and work collaboratively with others to both construct new systems on the latest and greatest platforms and to maintain and improve existing systems in a stable and thoughtful manner.Project Management:  I work closely with project managers to design & estimate solutions as well as track project timelines and allocate work.Mentoring:  I learn from my colleagues and make sure that they learn from me.  We work as a team and make sure that everyone has the knowledge and information they need to succeed.

As the primary developer on staff, I both maintained existing software, assisted with testing and deployment of new software, and rolled out new features and refactored code where necessary.  Some of my main challenges included: building and working with automated test suites to validate the functionality of both our website and API, architecting a multi-tenant site that balances customization with ease of maintenance, working with third-party providers to deliver solutions as needed, and working with our other staff to discern requirements and enhance our products.
Among other tasks, I worked with SQL and SSRS to develop a robust reporting solution to replace Crystal Reports.

I work alone and with a team to analyze the needs of our business partners, then to design, develop, and test in-house software solutions.  I have used VB.Net quite extensively to implement Business Objects, backed by a SQL 2005 database, for an in-house solution.  Currently, I am using Java in a team environment to customize a vendor package.
Worked in a small team on process refinement, implementation of standards, and tier-2 issue resolution for IT assets.
